WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:04.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Hello I'm Chantel Westerman
for Wisdom Television.

00:00:04.340 --> 00:00:07.520 align:middle line:84%
Welcome to our "Wisdom
Workshop" series.

00:00:07.520 --> 00:00:10.460 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting to note
that in the last 18 months,

00:00:10.460 --> 00:00:12.710 align:middle line:84%
nearly a quarter
of a million people

00:00:12.710 --> 00:00:14.390 align:middle line:84%
have come to Whole
Life Expos looking

00:00:14.390 --> 00:00:17.390 align:middle line:84%
for information about natural
health, personal growth,

00:00:17.390 --> 00:00:18.920 align:middle line:90%
and global change.

00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:21.380 align:middle line:84%
Today, I'd like to
invite you to join me

00:00:21.380 --> 00:00:23.870 align:middle line:84%
as I walk the floor
of a Whole Life Expo,

00:00:23.870 --> 00:00:25.790 align:middle line:84%
attending the
workshops, and meeting

00:00:25.790 --> 00:00:28.980 align:middle line:84%
some of the best-selling
authors in the field.

00:00:28.980 --> 00:00:30.560 align:middle line:90%
You may be surprised.

00:00:30.560 --> 00:00:33.500 align:middle line:84%
This world is a
lot more mainstream

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:36.812 align:middle line:90%
than you ever thought.

00:00:36.812 --> 00:00:39.800 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:39.800 --> 00:01:53.580 align:middle line:90%


00:01:53.580 --> 00:01:56.160 align:middle line:84%
In Phoenix, Whole
Life Expo attendees

00:01:56.160 --> 00:01:57.960 align:middle line:84%
were treated to
a special event--

00:01:57.960 --> 00:02:03.756 align:middle line:90%


00:02:03.756 --> 00:02:09.042 align:middle line:84%
an appearance by the Tibetan
monks of Drepung Loseling.

00:02:09.042 --> 00:02:11.886 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:11.886 --> 00:02:13.308 align:middle line:90%


00:02:13.308 --> 00:02:16.250 align:middle line:84%
The monks are
particularly renowned

00:02:16.250 --> 00:02:18.415 align:middle line:90%
for their multiphonic singing.

00:02:18.415 --> 00:02:20.690 align:middle line:90%
[THROAT SINGING]

00:02:20.690 --> 00:02:22.510 align:middle line:90%


00:02:22.510 --> 00:02:27.040 align:middle line:84%
Each chant master simultaneously
intones three notes, thus

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:31.402 align:middle line:84%
creating a complete
cord with one voice.

00:02:31.402 --> 00:02:34.366 align:middle line:90%
[THROAT SINGING]

00:02:34.366 --> 00:02:42.764 align:middle line:90%


00:02:42.764 --> 00:02:45.728 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:45.728 --> 00:02:51.680 align:middle line:90%


00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:54.140 align:middle line:84%
In the Dance of the
Black Hat Masters,

00:02:54.140 --> 00:02:56.715 align:middle line:84%
the performers rejoice
in the elimination

00:02:56.715 --> 00:02:57.590 align:middle line:90%
of negative energies.

00:02:57.590 --> 00:03:07.590 align:middle line:90%


00:03:07.590 --> 00:03:10.840 align:middle line:84%
The Playful Yak Dance
symbolizes the joy

00:03:10.840 --> 00:03:13.170 align:middle line:84%
of all living creatures
when humans entered

00:03:13.170 --> 00:03:14.950 align:middle line:90%
the realm of balanced living.

00:03:14.950 --> 00:03:30.860 align:middle line:90%


00:03:30.860 --> 00:03:34.130 align:middle line:84%
The Lamas also demonstrate
a traditional form

00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:36.090 align:middle line:90%
of monastic inquiry.

00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:37.850 align:middle line:84%
It's a lively debate
that brings them

00:03:37.850 --> 00:03:42.110 align:middle line:84%
to deeper levels of
spiritual understanding.

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:57.030 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:03:57.030 --> 00:04:00.181 align:middle line:84%
>> We'll see more from the
monks later in the program.

00:04:00.181 --> 00:04:02.105 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:04:02.105 --> 00:04:05.472 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:05.472 --> 00:04:09.330 align:middle line:90%


00:04:09.330 --> 00:04:15.450 align:middle line:84%
>> I often would hear people go
to God asking God to send them

00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:16.920 align:middle line:90%
a relationship.

00:04:16.920 --> 00:04:20.160 align:middle line:84%
But I noticed that once
a relationship got here,

00:04:20.160 --> 00:04:23.910 align:middle line:84%
how often they stopped talking
to God after that point.

00:04:23.910 --> 00:04:27.360 align:middle line:10%
You sort of see it symbolized
in the marriage ceremony.

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:29.790 align:middle line:10%
You go to the
synagogue or the church

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:33.360 align:middle line:10%
on the day of the wedding,
but then you don't necessarily

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:34.990 align:middle line:10%
go back.

00:04:34.990 --> 00:04:39.930 align:middle line:84%
There's this sense that we ask
God to send us a relationship.

00:04:39.930 --> 00:04:43.740 align:middle line:84%
We might even thank God
for the fact that He did.

00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:48.780 align:middle line:84%
But how little we actually
make the sacred dimension

00:04:48.780 --> 00:04:53.940 align:middle line:84%
of our lives a part of
our deepest relationships.

00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:57.960 align:middle line:84%
Now, the modern
world, particularly

00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:00.150 align:middle line:84%
under the Christian
dispensation,

00:05:00.150 --> 00:05:04.140 align:middle line:84%
has seen God over here
and sex over there.

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:06.840 align:middle line:84%
That's a large part
of the issue, which

00:05:06.840 --> 00:05:10.720 align:middle line:84%
has led us to think of
our romantic lives very,

00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:14.400 align:middle line:84%
very separately from
our sacred lives.

00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:18.960 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm interested in is,
what role does spirituality

00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:22.680 align:middle line:90%
play in our romantic journey?

00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:25.380 align:middle line:84%
And what role does
our romantic journey

00:05:25.380 --> 00:05:28.920 align:middle line:90%
play in our spiritual lives?

00:05:28.920 --> 00:05:32.710 align:middle line:10%
I know that I've had the
experience-- as many of us,

00:05:32.710 --> 00:05:34.620 align:middle line:10%
if not all of us have--

00:05:34.620 --> 00:05:37.770 align:middle line:10%
of having been
very much in love.

00:05:37.770 --> 00:05:40.590 align:middle line:10%
And then, after a
certain period of time,

00:05:40.590 --> 00:05:44.670 align:middle line:10%
if a certain something didn't
continue, the world would say,

00:05:44.670 --> 00:05:48.030 align:middle line:10%
well, you know,
that wasn't real.

00:05:48.030 --> 00:05:49.170 align:middle line:90%
That wasn't real.

00:05:49.170 --> 00:05:50.880 align:middle line:90%
That was just a delusion.

00:05:50.880 --> 00:05:55.320 align:middle line:84%
That was just an infatuation,
and then reality set in.

00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:57.790 align:middle line:90%
You've had that experience?

00:05:57.790 --> 00:05:59.970 align:middle line:10%
But I've come to believe,
at this point in my life,

00:05:59.970 --> 00:06:03.600 align:middle line:10%
that that is the exact
opposite of the truth.

00:06:03.600 --> 00:06:05.700 align:middle line:90%
That was not delusion.

00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:08.670 align:middle line:90%
That was reality.

00:06:08.670 --> 00:06:12.240 align:middle line:10%
And then non-reality set in.

00:06:12.240 --> 00:06:15.150 align:middle line:84%
So there's Jennifer,
and there's John.

00:06:15.150 --> 00:06:17.680 align:middle line:84%
So how does the Holy
Spirit make assignments?

00:06:17.680 --> 00:06:19.740 align:middle line:84%
Well, theoretically,
the Holy Spirit

00:06:19.740 --> 00:06:23.670 align:middle line:84%
sees Jennifer and goes,
what Jennifer most needs

00:06:23.670 --> 00:06:28.350 align:middle line:84%
to learn in her life is
blah, blah, blah, blah.

00:06:28.350 --> 00:06:32.370 align:middle line:84%
And John-- John could be
in Timbuktu at that moment,

00:06:32.370 --> 00:06:34.230 align:middle line:84%
but the universe
says, John needs

00:06:34.230 --> 00:06:36.730 align:middle line:84%
to learn blah, blah,
blah, blah, blah, blah.

00:06:36.730 --> 00:06:40.830 align:middle line:84%
Now, if Jennifer and
John knew each other,

00:06:40.830 --> 00:06:43.660 align:middle line:84%
that would provide the
maximal opportunities.

00:06:43.660 --> 00:06:47.130 align:middle line:84%
There's no one better
than John for Jennifer

00:06:47.130 --> 00:06:48.820 align:middle line:90%
to learn with it this time.

00:06:48.820 --> 00:06:51.510 align:middle line:84%
There's no one better
than Jennifer than John

00:06:51.510 --> 00:06:54.183 align:middle line:90%
to learn with at this time.

00:06:54.183 --> 00:06:56.100 align:middle line:84%
And so the notion here
is that the universe is

00:06:56.100 --> 00:06:58.570 align:middle line:90%
like a gigantic bio-computer.

00:06:58.570 --> 00:07:01.080 align:middle line:84%
And so the universe
then conspires.

00:07:01.080 --> 00:07:05.760 align:middle line:84%
John might think he's going to
spend the summer in Timbuktu.

00:07:05.760 --> 00:07:06.870 align:middle line:90%
Ha!

00:07:06.870 --> 00:07:09.990 align:middle line:84%
Because he's needed to meet
Jennifer at her cousin's

00:07:09.990 --> 00:07:12.730 align:middle line:90%
wedding in Cleveland.

00:07:12.730 --> 00:07:13.530 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:07:13.530 --> 00:07:17.850 align:middle line:84%
So those two will be brought
together by cosmic forces.

00:07:17.850 --> 00:07:21.810 align:middle line:84%
Now, that is to say that
they are destined to meet.

00:07:21.810 --> 00:07:25.240 align:middle line:84%
That is not to say that they
are destined to stay together.

00:07:25.240 --> 00:07:29.650 align:middle line:84%
Free will-- you know,
karma says you will meet.

00:07:29.650 --> 00:07:34.950 align:middle line:84%
Free will says what you will
do with the opportunity.

00:07:34.950 --> 00:07:37.300 align:middle line:84%
Now, what's going
on inside Jennifer,

00:07:37.300 --> 00:07:39.480 align:middle line:90%
and what's going on inside John?

00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:42.840 align:middle line:84%
Well, Jennifer and John are
just like the rest of us.

00:07:42.840 --> 00:07:51.700 align:middle line:84%
Deep in their hearts, they yearn
for the deepest, truest love.

00:07:51.700 --> 00:07:52.700 align:middle line:90%
How do I know that?

00:07:52.700 --> 00:07:55.250 align:middle line:84%
Because Jennifer
and John are human.

00:07:55.250 --> 00:07:57.310 align:middle line:10%
In "A Course in
Miracles," it says

00:07:57.310 --> 00:08:00.220 align:middle line:10%
that our love for another
person, our deepest

00:08:00.220 --> 00:08:05.260 align:middle line:10%
passion for another
person, is but a shadow--

00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:08.620 align:middle line:10%
it's a shadow-- of
our love for God.

00:08:08.620 --> 00:08:10.180 align:middle line:84%
You know, in "Les
Miserable," there's

00:08:10.180 --> 00:08:16.330 align:middle line:84%
that song where the words
go "to love another person

00:08:16.330 --> 00:08:19.750 align:middle line:90%
is to see the face of God."

00:08:19.750 --> 00:08:21.880 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's a Heaven
that we yearn for.

00:08:21.880 --> 00:08:24.340 align:middle line:84%
"The Course in Miracles"
says Heaven is not

00:08:24.340 --> 00:08:25.750 align:middle line:90%
a place or condition.

00:08:25.750 --> 00:08:28.190 align:middle line:90%
It's an awareness.

00:08:28.190 --> 00:08:30.310 align:middle line:84%
And when we fall in
love with somebody,

00:08:30.310 --> 00:08:34.720 align:middle line:84%
we have an awareness of
our oneness with them.

00:08:34.720 --> 00:08:38.690 align:middle line:84%
We have a merger on the
deepest level of our souls.

00:08:38.690 --> 00:08:42.320 align:middle line:84%
We bypass boundaries, not
in a dysfunctional way,

00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:45.430 align:middle line:84%
but in the highest,
most transcendent way.

00:08:45.430 --> 00:08:49.780 align:middle line:84%
And we experience our oneness
with another human being.

00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:55.320 align:middle line:84%
And if enough of us do that,
all Heaven breaks loose.

00:08:55.320 --> 00:08:57.660 align:middle line:84%
So notice, a girlfriend
of mine once said,

00:08:57.660 --> 00:09:00.920 align:middle line:84%
I can only be with a man so long
before I have to kill him off.

00:09:00.920 --> 00:09:03.570 align:middle line:90%


00:09:03.570 --> 00:09:07.890 align:middle line:84%
I can only be with a man so long
before the color of his socks

00:09:07.890 --> 00:09:10.590 align:middle line:90%
starts bothering me.

00:09:10.590 --> 00:09:14.970 align:middle line:84%
I can only be with a man
so long before the fact

00:09:14.970 --> 00:09:18.510 align:middle line:84%
that he is not a perfect
human being becomes

00:09:18.510 --> 00:09:21.540 align:middle line:90%
an unbearable fact to me.

00:09:21.540 --> 00:09:24.360 align:middle line:84%
As I say often, if
you're not perfect,

00:09:24.360 --> 00:09:28.230 align:middle line:84%
what perfect person
do you think is

00:09:28.230 --> 00:09:30.860 align:middle line:90%
going to show up in your life.

00:09:30.860 --> 00:09:32.280 align:middle line:90%
You're not perfect.

00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:34.030 align:middle line:90%
Why would they be perfect?

00:09:34.030 --> 00:09:36.810 align:middle line:84%
And that's not even
to mention that I just

00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:41.128 align:middle line:84%
don't think there are that many
enlightened masters dating.

00:09:41.128 --> 00:09:42.170 align:middle line:90%
You know what I'm saying?

00:09:42.170 --> 00:09:45.130 align:middle line:90%


00:09:45.130 --> 00:09:48.100 align:middle line:84%
So what kind of
situation is this

00:09:48.100 --> 00:09:51.180 align:middle line:84%
if we have no hope
of holding on to love

00:09:51.180 --> 00:09:56.690 align:middle line:84%
if someone not being perfect is
such a bitter disappointment?

00:09:56.690 --> 00:09:59.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, what we are given,
from a spiritual perspective,

00:09:59.650 --> 00:10:03.070 align:middle line:84%
is the notion that the whole
point of the relationship

00:10:03.070 --> 00:10:05.470 align:middle line:84%
is that we are
here to be healed.

00:10:05.470 --> 00:10:09.310 align:middle line:84%
That is, in fact, why
John and Jennifer met.

00:10:09.310 --> 00:10:12.850 align:middle line:84%
Jennifer is thinking, on
some level of her mind,

00:10:12.850 --> 00:10:19.620 align:middle line:84%
I want to meet a man in whose
love I can forget my wounds.

00:10:19.620 --> 00:10:23.470 align:middle line:84%
And God is saying, I'm
going to send Jennifer

00:10:23.470 --> 00:10:28.810 align:middle line:84%
a man with whom she
can address her wounds.

00:10:28.810 --> 00:10:31.060 align:middle line:84%
But she will only
be able to address

00:10:31.060 --> 00:10:35.890 align:middle line:84%
her wounds in a situation
where they come up.

00:10:35.890 --> 00:10:38.950 align:middle line:84%
So then, Jennifer might later
say, I don't like this guy.

00:10:38.950 --> 00:10:40.870 align:middle line:90%
He wounded me.

00:10:40.870 --> 00:10:43.240 align:middle line:84%
When the truth of the matter
is he didn't wound her.

00:10:43.240 --> 00:10:48.010 align:middle line:84%
He triggered her wounds that
she had before she even met him.

00:10:48.010 --> 00:10:50.140 align:middle line:84%
And they had to be
triggered in order for her

00:10:50.140 --> 00:10:54.940 align:middle line:84%
to take a good look at them,
for her to forgive whoever--

00:10:54.940 --> 00:10:57.740 align:middle line:84%
whether it was someone
else or herself.

00:10:57.740 --> 00:11:00.860 align:middle line:84%
Which now, at this
time, her mind probably

00:11:00.860 --> 00:11:03.280 align:middle line:84%
is projecting it wasn't someone
else, and it wasn't her.

00:11:03.280 --> 00:11:05.900 align:middle line:90%
It was John.

00:11:05.900 --> 00:11:09.310 align:middle line:84%
And so she now has the
opportunity to heal.

00:11:09.310 --> 00:11:12.040 align:middle line:84%
But what usually happens,
or happens so often?

00:11:12.040 --> 00:11:14.450 align:middle line:84%
At that point,
John says, I can't

00:11:14.450 --> 00:11:15.700 align:middle line:90%
deal with this woman's issues.

00:11:15.700 --> 00:11:18.460 align:middle line:90%


00:11:18.460 --> 00:11:21.340 align:middle line:84%
Or Jennifer says, I don't like
the way this guy makes me feel.

00:11:21.340 --> 00:11:22.840 align:middle line:84%
What she's really
saying is, I don't

00:11:22.840 --> 00:11:26.380 align:middle line:84%
like the way the last 30 years
of my life have made me feel,

00:11:26.380 --> 00:11:28.690 align:middle line:90%
but I'm coping.

00:11:28.690 --> 00:11:30.670 align:middle line:84%
But in his presence,
I can't even cope,

00:11:30.670 --> 00:11:32.163 align:middle line:90%
it comes up so strong.

00:11:32.163 --> 00:11:33.580 align:middle line:84%
In "A Course in
Miracles," this is

00:11:33.580 --> 00:11:36.160 align:middle line:84%
called the difference between
a special relationship

00:11:36.160 --> 00:11:38.350 align:middle line:90%
and a holy relationship.

00:11:38.350 --> 00:11:44.470 align:middle line:84%
A special relationship is where
Jennifer's ego meets John's ego

00:11:44.470 --> 00:11:47.647 align:middle line:84%
and where Jennifer wants
John to be perfect somehow.

00:11:47.647 --> 00:11:49.480 align:middle line:84%
And she wants to hide
her own imperfections,

00:11:49.480 --> 00:11:51.772 align:middle line:84%
because she figures if John
saw what she's really like,

00:11:51.772 --> 00:11:53.260 align:middle line:90%
he would probably reject her.

00:11:53.260 --> 00:11:55.240 align:middle line:84%
And John is doing the
same thing to Jennifer.

00:11:55.240 --> 00:11:58.240 align:middle line:84%
And if either one of them had
the audacity or the misfortune

00:11:58.240 --> 00:11:59.950 align:middle line:84%
to show up as a
real human being,

00:11:59.950 --> 00:12:02.690 align:middle line:90%
they are likely to be rejected.

00:12:02.690 --> 00:12:07.100 align:middle line:10%
A holy relationship is where
John and Jennifer understand,

00:12:07.100 --> 00:12:09.840 align:middle line:10%
we both are wounded.

00:12:09.840 --> 00:12:11.840 align:middle line:90%
That's why we were sent here.

00:12:11.840 --> 00:12:16.350 align:middle line:84%
Our love can be a
hospital for our souls.

00:12:16.350 --> 00:12:18.630 align:middle line:84%
And your stuff's
going to come up,

00:12:18.630 --> 00:12:21.090 align:middle line:90%
and my stuff's going to come up.

00:12:21.090 --> 00:12:24.760 align:middle line:84%
Often, not because we're
not meant for each other,

00:12:24.760 --> 00:12:27.380 align:middle line:90%
but because we are.

00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:32.650 align:middle line:84%
But we can make of this
relationship a sanctuary.

00:12:32.650 --> 00:12:35.620 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:35.620 --> 00:12:37.610 align:middle line:90%


00:12:37.610 --> 00:12:41.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, Mary, I come into
this a little bit skeptically.

00:12:41.900 --> 00:12:45.050 align:middle line:84%
But I think my skepticism
comes from not knowing

00:12:45.050 --> 00:12:48.230 align:middle line:90%
what aura video vision is.

00:12:48.230 --> 00:12:51.770 align:middle line:84%
>> This system will allow you
to interact live with your aura.

00:12:51.770 --> 00:12:54.530 align:middle line:10%
You'll actually be able to see
it live and what's happening

00:12:54.530 --> 00:12:55.520 align:middle line:10%
and what's going on--

00:12:55.520 --> 00:12:58.110 align:middle line:10%
all the responses to your
emotional, your mental,

00:12:58.110 --> 00:12:59.610 align:middle line:10%
and some of your
physical, as well.

00:12:59.610 --> 00:13:00.830 align:middle line:84%
So as we're talking
about different things,

00:13:00.830 --> 00:13:02.600 align:middle line:84%
you're actually
going to see a change

00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:04.740 align:middle line:84%
and alter on screen
while that's happening.

00:13:04.740 --> 00:13:06.830 align:middle line:90%
>> What is an aura, exactly?

00:13:06.830 --> 00:13:09.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Basically, an aura is the
electromagnetic energy field

