amount of multivitamins

00:30:25.620 --> 00:30:27.390 align:middle line:90%
to prevent deficiency disease.

00:30:27.390 --> 00:30:29.160 align:middle line:84%
So I take a
multivitamin every day,

00:30:29.160 --> 00:30:30.930 align:middle line:84%
and I tell my patients
to take what's

00:30:30.930 --> 00:30:34.570 align:middle line:84%
called an RDA, or daily
value, multivitamin every day.

00:30:34.570 --> 00:30:36.990 align:middle line:84%
But in addition, there
are more vitamins

00:30:36.990 --> 00:30:40.320 align:middle line:84%
that you take that
help optimize health,

00:30:40.320 --> 00:30:43.560 align:middle line:84%
and it's a pretty easy
mnemonic to remember--

00:30:43.560 --> 00:30:47.940 align:middle line:90%
CDEF, calcium and magnesium.

00:30:47.940 --> 00:30:52.560 align:middle line:84%
So it's the alphabet, CDEF,
and then calcium and magnesium

00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:53.760 align:middle line:90%
and the number 400.

00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:55.260 align:middle line:90%
>> What does F do for us?

00:30:55.260 --> 00:30:58.920 align:middle line:84%
>> F is not vitamin F, but
it's folic acid, or folate.

00:30:58.920 --> 00:31:00.030 align:middle line:90%
It's a B vitamin.

00:31:00.030 --> 00:31:03.692 align:middle line:84%
I just remember it that way,
because it fits with CDEF.

00:31:03.692 --> 00:31:07.110 align:middle line:84%
And the second part you have
to remember is the number 400.

00:31:07.110 --> 00:31:08.850 align:middle line:90%
So even I can remember this.

00:31:08.850 --> 00:31:12.850 align:middle line:84%
400 milligrams of vitamin
C three times a day.

00:31:12.850 --> 00:31:14.790 align:middle line:84%
Why do you need it
more than once a day?

00:31:14.790 --> 00:31:17.530 align:middle line:84%
Because it's water soluble,
and you urinate it out.

00:31:17.530 --> 00:31:20.280 align:middle line:84%
So in order to keep a
steady level, you need 400,

00:31:20.280 --> 00:31:22.740 align:middle line:84%
and you need it
three times a day.

00:31:22.740 --> 00:31:26.550 align:middle line:84%
Vitamin D, 400 international
units once a day.

00:31:26.550 --> 00:31:30.090 align:middle line:84%
Vitamin E, 400 international
units once a day.

00:31:30.090 --> 00:31:36.030 align:middle line:84%
Folate, or folic acid, 400 mcg
more than a diet once a day.

00:31:36.030 --> 00:31:38.250 align:middle line:90%
Calcium, 400 three times a day.

00:31:38.250 --> 00:31:39.625 align:middle line:84%
Calcium you can
take all at once.

00:31:39.625 --> 00:31:40.958 align:middle line:90%
You don't need to spread it out.

00:31:40.958 --> 00:31:42.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Especially for women.

00:31:42.080 --> 00:31:43.280 align:middle line:90%
>> And magnesium, 400.

00:31:43.280 --> 00:31:46.213 align:middle line:84%
Well, calcium is very
important for men, too.

00:31:46.213 --> 00:31:48.630 align:middle line:84%
The reason we think it's more
important-- the reason we've

00:31:48.630 --> 00:31:50.340 align:middle line:84%
associate it's more
important with women

00:31:50.340 --> 00:31:53.190 align:middle line:84%
is because women tend
to live longer than men.

00:31:53.190 --> 00:31:57.870 align:middle line:84%
And it's in their older age
that they get osteoarthritis

00:31:57.870 --> 00:32:01.740 align:middle line:84%
and they get osteoporosis,
both of which

00:32:01.740 --> 00:32:04.410 align:middle line:84%
are helped greatly
by having calcium.

00:32:04.410 --> 00:32:07.920 align:middle line:84%
Men build up bigger bones
when they're younger.

00:32:07.920 --> 00:32:09.670 align:middle line:84%
So when they fall
when they get older,

00:32:09.670 --> 00:32:11.820 align:middle line:84%
they don't have quite
the number of fractures.

00:32:11.820 --> 00:32:15.400 align:middle line:84%
And they die of other
things before women.

00:32:15.400 --> 00:32:18.810 align:middle line:84%
So, in fact, we've thought it
isn't as important for men,

00:32:18.810 --> 00:32:20.980 align:middle line:84%
but it's just as
important for men.

00:32:20.980 --> 00:32:22.920 align:middle line:84%
And it's especially
important preventing

00:32:22.920 --> 00:32:24.780 align:middle line:90%
arthritis or osteoarthritis.

00:32:24.780 --> 00:32:29.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Do women or men
age more quickly?

00:32:29.050 --> 00:32:34.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it turns out that
until age 50, men age quicker.

00:32:34.950 --> 00:32:38.820 align:middle line:84%
And then, those women who
don't take hormone replacement

00:32:38.820 --> 00:32:40.920 align:middle line:90%
therapy age quicker.

00:32:40.920 --> 00:32:44.100 align:middle line:84%
By age 66, men and
women catch up.

00:32:44.100 --> 00:32:47.040 align:middle line:84%
Now, men never quite
catch up to women,

00:32:47.040 --> 00:32:49.750 align:middle line:84%
and that's why women
tend to live longer.

00:32:49.750 --> 00:32:55.470 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, right now, in the
RealAge book, as we look at it,

00:32:55.470 --> 00:32:59.430 align:middle line:84%
both men and women can change
their rate of aging greatly.

00:32:59.430 --> 00:33:02.020 align:middle line:84%
And in the last 12
years in America,

00:33:02.020 --> 00:33:05.460 align:middle line:84%
in fact, men have aged as
a group, believe it or not,

00:33:05.460 --> 00:33:07.560 align:middle line:90%
only 9.7 years--

00:33:07.560 --> 00:33:10.500 align:middle line:90%
women, about 10.9 years.

00:33:10.500 --> 00:33:13.200 align:middle line:84%
So men are doing
things to catch up

00:33:13.200 --> 00:33:15.900 align:middle line:84%
to the slower rate of
aging that women have now.

00:33:15.900 --> 00:33:19.110 align:middle line:84%
>> So if the world stood
still right now, Michael,

00:33:19.110 --> 00:33:24.720 align:middle line:84%
and everybody was listening to
you and everybody could hear,

00:33:24.720 --> 00:33:27.690 align:middle line:84%
would you give men different
advice than you would women

00:33:27.690 --> 00:33:29.400 align:middle line:90%
in terms of aging?

00:33:29.400 --> 00:33:31.530 align:middle line:84%
>> No, I'd give everyone
the same advice.

00:33:31.530 --> 00:33:35.610 align:middle line:84%
Take the RealAge program,
find out your options,

00:33:35.610 --> 00:33:37.610 align:middle line:90%
and then choose some you want.

00:33:37.610 --> 00:33:39.510 align:middle line:84%
Because what is
easy for you may be

00:33:39.510 --> 00:33:41.740 align:middle line:90%
difficult for me and vice versa.

00:33:41.740 --> 00:33:44.640 align:middle line:84%
But we all have some
things that we can

00:33:44.640 --> 00:33:46.320 align:middle line:90%
do that are relatively easy.

00:33:46.320 --> 00:33:50.010 align:middle line:84%
My most successful patients
start with three or four things

00:33:50.010 --> 00:33:52.050 align:middle line:84%
from the RealAge book--
read the chapters

00:33:52.050 --> 00:33:53.880 align:middle line:84%
as well as pick
them out, so they

00:33:53.880 --> 00:33:55.890 align:middle line:90%
know and understand what to do.

00:33:55.890 --> 00:33:57.690 align:middle line:84%
Then, after 90
days, they're doing

00:33:57.690 --> 00:34:00.240 align:middle line:84%
two or three of the three or
four things they've chosen,

00:34:00.240 --> 00:34:01.350 align:middle line:90%
and they add one.

00:34:01.350 --> 00:34:02.760 align:middle line:90%
And they incrementally add.

00:34:02.760 --> 00:34:04.830 align:middle line:84%
And pretty soon, they're
getting much younger

00:34:04.830 --> 00:34:07.350 align:middle line:84%
and feeling more
vigorous and knowing

00:34:07.350 --> 00:34:10.590 align:middle line:84%
that they'll be around to
care for their loved ones,

00:34:10.590 --> 00:34:14.696 align:middle line:84%
rather than having to be
cared for by their loved ones.

